parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The extremely loud screeching/pounding noise from the speakers can be a distraction while driving, potentially causing accidents or disrupting the driver's ability to focus on the road.
symptoms: Loud screeching/pounding noise from the speakers
even when the volume is turned down or the radio is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent disengagement of the air recirculation system can cause outside air and toxic odors to enter the cabin, potentially causing health concerns for the occupants.
symptoms: Air recirculation system disengages intermittently
allowing outside air and strong odors to enter the cabin
especially when the heat is activated in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable temperature swings can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents, especially when trailering or driving in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Temperature settings randomly swing wildly
causing extreme hot or cold temperatures
requiring frequent adjustments
and taking the driver's attention away from the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melted trailer plug can cause a loss of trailer brakes, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control while towing.
symptoms: Trailer plug melts at the connection to the truck
resulting in a message indicating the trailer is disconnected and has no brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Rear Seat Carpeting and Exposed Sharp Edges
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exposed sharp edges of the sheet metal in the rear seat area can cause injuries, such as cuts or lacerations, to occupants, especially children, when leaning into the area to retrieve items.
symptoms: Void areas in the rear seat carpeting
exposed sheet metal with sharp edges
potential for injury or harm to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Glass Shattering and Shards Entering the Cabin
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The windshield glass shattering and sending shards into the cabin can cause injuries to the driver and occupants, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Windshield glass shattering
glass shards entering the cabin
potential for injury or harm to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Pre-Collision Assist system can increase the risk of accidents, as the vehicle may not be able to alert the driver or take corrective action to prevent or mitigate collisions.
symptoms: The "Pre-Collision Assist Not Available" message is displayed on the dashboard
the Pre-Collision Assist system is inoperable
the system fails to alert the driver of potential collisions
the system fails to take corrective action to prevent or mitigate collisions.
